1095028485.text: "Coactivation of CD21 and BCR in human tonsillar B cells decreased Fas expression upon CD40 stimulus, increase the levels of anti-apoptotic Flip and Bcl-2 (but not BCL-xl) and reduced caspase-8 cleavage when compared to BCR activation alone However activation of mouse B cells by recombinant antigen fused with C3d 3 resulted in only an increase in expression level of FLIP but not Bcl-2."
